  "metadata": {
    "anchor_id": "member_b",
    "description": "34-year-old male, PPO plan. Knee injury → MRI denial → appeal → surgery → PT. 18-month longitudinal narrative (Jan–Oct 2025).",
    "created": "2026-03-04",
    "narrative_summary": "Marcus Thompson injured his right knee in January 2025. His PCP ordered an MRI, but the claim was denied in February for missing prior authorization. Marcus called member services, upset. An appeal was filed, and in March the appeal was won — the MRI was covered retroactively. A prior auth was then submitted and approved for knee arthroscopy. Surgery was performed in April. Physical therapy ran from May through October (approaching the 30-visit annual limit). One post-surgery pain medication prescription was filled. Two case notes document member services interactions, and one formal complaint was filed about the denial process."
  },

